Doing it that way is totally unnecessary.  Like I said in my first comment `col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-6` is the SAME as saying `col-xs-6`.  Col-xs-6 says - for screen size extra small and up, use 6 columns - and will do that until you set a different break point for a larger screen size.  So `col-xs-6 col-md-4` says - for extra small and small screens, use 6 columns, then for medium, large and extra large screens, use 4 columns.  It always starts at the smallest defined screen size and applies to all larger screens, unless told otherwise.
